1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
Here's what science actually says about mast cells.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:10,000
Mast cells are tiny defenders in your immune system, hidden in tissues like your skin and lungs.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,600
They release chemicals like histamine during allergic reactions — but that's just the beginning.

4
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:21,600
Recent studies show mast cells also play roles in wound healing and even cancer defense.

5
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:26,400
Understanding these cells could change how we treat allergies and inflammatory diseases.

6
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:29,200
Curious about how your body protects itself?

